'''''Friends in Love''''' is an [[album]] by American pop singer [[Johnny Mathis]] that was released in April 1982 by [[Columbia Records]].<ref name = "personal">(1993) ''The Music of Johnny Mathis: A Personal Collection'' by Johnny Mathis [CD booklet]. New York: Columbia Records C4K-48932.</ref> It made its first appearance on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine's [[Billboard 200|Top LP's & Tapes]] chart in the issue dated May 8, 1982, and remained there for nine weeks, peaking at number 147.<ref>{{Harvnb|Whitburn|2010|p=504}}.</ref> It also made it to number 34 during a seven-week run on the UK album chart that began the following week, on May 15.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/_/johnny%20mathis/|title= Johnny Mathis - Albums |publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=7 February 2014}}</ref>

The title track from the album entered the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] in the issue dated April 17, 1982, and eventually got as high as number 38 over the course of 13 weeks.<ref>{{Harvnb|Whitburn|2009|p=628}}.</ref> That same issue included its debut on the magazine's list of the 100 most popular [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|R&B]] songs in the US, where it also spent 13 weeks but reached number 22.<ref>{{Harvnb|Whitburn|2004|p=383}}.</ref> The next issue, dated April 24, marked its first appearance on the [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]] chart, and during its 17-week run there it rose to number five.<ref>{{Harvnb|Whitburn|2007|p=179}}.</ref>

This is the first Mathis album whose initial release included the [[Compact disc| compact disc]] (CD) format.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/friends-in-love-mw0000311641/releases|title=Friends in Love - Johnny Mathis, Dionne Warwick - Releases|work=allmusic.com|publisher=All Media Network, LLC|accessdate=8 February 2014}}</ref>

